properties.NAME: Deseret
properties.CHANGE: The General Assembly of the newly proposed state of Deseret met on 2 Jul 1849. The state was to include almost all of Utah and parts of present Ariz., Cal., Colo., Ida., Nev., N.Mex., Ore., and Wyo., but proposal never gained support in U.S. Congress.
properties.CITATION: (Atlas of Utah, 160-161; Brown, Cannon, and Jackson, 90-91; Swindler, 9:375-381)

properties.NAME: Mexican Cession
properties.CHANGE: Treaty of Guadalupe-Hidalgo ended the war between Mexico and the United States. Area ceded by Mexico became Unorganized Federal Territory (non-county area) in the United States.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 9, pp. 922-943; Parry, 102: 29-59; Van Zandt, 11, 28-29; Walker and Bufkin, 19, 20A)

properties.NAME: Utah
properties.CHANGE: The state of Utah was created from Utah Territory; Utah Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Utah Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Utah Territory from the territory ceded by Mexico in the Treaty of Guadalupe-Hidalgo (1848), from territory to be purchased from the state of Texas in December 1850, and from unorganized federal territory.

properties.NAME: Utah Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Colorado Territory from Nebraska, New Mexico, and Utah Territories, and from the former Kansas Territory.

properties.NAME: Utah Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Nevada Territory from Utah Territory. Utah Territory also lost to Nebraska Territory when Nebraska Territory gained area in present Wyoming from Utah Territory.

properties.NAME: Utah Territory
properties.CHANGE: Nevada Territory gained from Utah Territory.

properties.NAME: Utah Territory
properties.CHANGE: The state of Nevada gained from Utah Territory.

properties.NAME: Utah Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Wyoming Territory from Dakota, Idaho, and Utah Territories.
